DAX Index Futures Volume Surges to 25% of 30-Day Average in 30 Minutes

-- B y   A l e x i s   X y d i a s
-- 
2011-08-25T14:27:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-25/dax-index-futures-volume-surges-to-25-of-30-day-average-in-30-minutes.html
Futures on  Germany â€™s benchmark DAX
Index plunged as much as 4.1 percent as a cascade of
trades pushed the volume in the contracts to a quarter of the
daily average between 3:45 p.m. and 4:15 p.m. in  Frankfurt .  The futures fell 2.7 percent at 4:22 p.m. to 5,522. A total
of 50,000 contracts exchanged hands between 3:45 p.m. and 4:15
p.m., according to Bloomberg data. The average volume in the
past 30 days was 207,000, Bloomberg data show.  DAX futures plunged as much as 7.1 percent on Aug. 18 in a
move some traders attributed to the use of the contracts as a
hedge against wider pan-European market losses.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
